[[File:SmallAsteroidImpacts-Frequency-Bolide-20141114.jpg|thumb|upright=1.7|Frequency of [[bolide]]s, small asteroids roughly 1 to 20 meters in diameter impacting Earth's atmosphere]]{{main|Near-Earth object#Near-Earth asteroids|l1=Near-Earth asteroids}}
Near-Earth asteroids, or NEAs, are asteroids that have orbits that pass close to that of Earth. Asteroids that actually cross Earth's orbital path are known as ''Earth-crossers''. {{As of|2016|06}}, 14,464 near-Earth asteroids are known<ref name=nasa_neo>{{cite web |title=Discovery Statistics |url=http://neo.jpl.nasa.gov/stats/ |website=CNEOS |accessdate=15 June 2016}}</ref> and the number over one kilometer in diameter is estimated to be 900–1,000.

